Business Brief -- McCormick  Co.:
   Spice, Flavoring Firm's Net
   Rose 18% in 4th Quarter
For the year, net rose to $80.9 million, or $1.96 a share,
from $69.4 million, or $1.66 a share. Fiscal 1990 figures
included a gain of $6.3 million, or 15 cents a share, on the
sale of property in Britain. Annual sales also rose 8%, to
$1.43 billion.
   McCormick recently announced a 2-for-1 stock split that
will be effective Jan. 17. Fiscal 1992 first-quarter earnings
will reflect that split.